---
import ContentLayout from '../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import { useTranslations } from '../../i18n/ui';

const lang = 'en';
const t = useTranslations(lang);

const structuredData = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'HowTo',
  name: 'How to set up OpenClaw with Claude Pro on a VPS',
  description: 'Complete guide to install and configure OpenClaw, the open-source autonomous AI assistant, on an affordable VPS with Claude Pro.',
  inLanguage: 'en',
  totalTime: 'PT45M',
  tool: [
    { '@type': 'HowToTool', name: 'OpenClaw' },
    { '@type': 'HowToTool', name: 'Docker' },
    { '@type': 'HowToTool', name: 'VPS (DigitalOcean or similar)' },
  ],
};
---

<ContentLayout
  title={`OpenClaw: Your Personal AI Assistant | ${t.siteTitle}`}
  description="Complete guide to install OpenClaw on an affordable VPS with Claude Pro. Learn how to have your own autonomous AI assistant accessible from WhatsApp, Telegram and more."
  lang={lang}
  currentPath="openclaw"
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <h1>OpenClaw: Your Personal AI Assistant</h1>
  <p class="lead">Set up your own autonomous AI agent on an affordable VPS, accessible from WhatsApp, Telegram and more, using your Claude Pro subscription.</p>

  <nav class="toc">
    <h2>Contents</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#what-is">What is OpenClaw?</a></li>
      <li><a href="#benefits">Benefits of OpenClaw</a></li>
      <li><a href="#requirements">Requirements</a></li>
      <li><a href="#vps">Choosing a VPS</a></li>
      <li><a href="#installation">Step-by-Step Installation</a></li>
      <li><a href="#claude-pro">Connect with Claude Pro</a></li>
      <li><a href="#messaging">Connect Messaging Platform</a></li>
      <li><a href="#security">Security and Best Practices</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>

  <section id="what-is">
    <h2>What is OpenClaw?</h2>

    <p><a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenClaw</a> (formerly known as Clawdbot and Moltbot) is a <strong>free, open-source autonomous AI agent</strong> that works as your personal assistant. Unlike using Claude in the browser, OpenClaw:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Lives in your messaging apps</strong> - Talk to your AI from WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, Slack, Signal, iMessage and more</li>
      <li><strong>Executes tasks on your machine</strong> - Can read/write files, run commands, browse the web</li>
      <li><strong>Works autonomously</strong> - You can schedule automated tasks with cron jobs</li>
      <li><strong>Remembers everything</strong> - Has persistent memory across conversations</li>
      <li><strong>Is self-hosted</strong> - You control your data, it runs on your own server</li>
    </ul>

    <p>It's one of the fastest-growing open-source projects, with over <strong>145,000 GitHub stars</strong>.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <p><strong>In a nutshell:</strong> Imagine having Claude available 24/7 from your WhatsApp, able to execute code, automate tasks, and remember your preferences. That's OpenClaw.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="benefits">
    <h2>Benefits of OpenClaw</h2>

    <div class="feature-grid">
      <div class="feature-item">
        <h3>Natural Conversation</h3>
        <p>Talk to your AI from the apps you already use. No need to open a browser or terminal - just send a WhatsApp message.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-item">
        <h3>Always Available</h3>
        <p>Running on a VPS, your assistant is online 24/7. You can ask things at 3 AM or schedule automated tasks.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-item">
        <h3>Full Privacy</h3>
        <p>You control the server. Your conversations and data don't pass through third parties beyond your chosen AI provider.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-item">
        <h3>Automation</h3>
        <p>Schedule recurring tasks: monitor your email, generate reports, run backups, watch prices, and much more.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-item">
        <h3>Multi-Model</h3>
        <p>Not limited to one model. Supports Claude, GPT-4o, Gemini, DeepSeek, and local models with Ollama.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-item">
        <h3>Extensible</h3>
        <p>"Skills" system (plugins) that extend capabilities: browser automation, calendar management, code review, and more.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="requirements">
    <h2>Requirements</h2>

    <p>To follow this guide you'll need:</p>

    <ol>
      <li><strong>A Claude Pro subscription</strong> ($20/month) or Max ($100/month) - <a href="/en/tools">see plans</a></li>
      <li><strong>A VPS</strong> (virtual private server) - from $4-6/month</li>
      <li><strong>An account on a messaging platform</strong> - WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, etc.</li>
      <li><strong>Basic terminal knowledge</strong> - ability to run commands (what you've learned in this guide)</li>
    </ol>

    <p><strong>Total monthly cost:</strong> ~$24-26/month (Claude Pro + budget VPS)</p>
  </section>

  <section id="vps">
    <h2>Choosing a VPS</h2>

    <p>A VPS (Virtual Private Server) is a cloud computer that's running 24/7. For OpenClaw you need very little:</p>

    <table class="pricing-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Provider</th>
          <th>Price/month</th>
          <th>RAM</th>
          <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>DigitalOcean</strong></td>
          <td>$6</td>
          <td>1 GB</td>
          <td>1-Click deploy available for OpenClaw</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Hostinger</strong></td>
          <td>$4-5</td>
          <td>2 GB</td>
          <td>Docker template for OpenClaw</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Hetzner</strong></td>
          <td>€4</td>
          <td>2 GB</td>
          <td>Excellent price/performance ratio</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Vultr</strong></td>
          <td>$5</td>
          <td>1 GB</td>
          <td>Many locations available</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="callout">
      <p><strong>Recommendation:</strong> If it's your first time, <a href="https://www.digitalocean.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DigitalOcean</a> is the easiest option because it has a 1-Click deploy for OpenClaw. If you want to save money, <a href="https://www.hetzner.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hetzner</a> offers more resources for less.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Minimum VPS Requirements</h3>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Operating system:</strong> Ubuntu 22.04 or 24.04 LTS</li>
      <li><strong>RAM:</strong> 2 GB (minimum 1 GB, recommended 2 GB+)</li>
      <li><strong>Disk:</strong> 10 GB or more</li>
      <li><strong>CPU:</strong> 1 vCPU is enough</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="installation">
    <h2>Step-by-Step Installation</h2>

    <p>We'll install OpenClaw using Docker, which is the simplest and recommended method for a VPS.</p>

    <h3>1. Connect to your VPS</h3>

    <p>Open your terminal and connect to your VPS via SSH:</p>

    <CodeBlock
      code={`ssh root@YOUR-VPS-IP`}
      language="bash"
      filename="Terminal (your computer)"
    />

    <h3>2. Install Docker</h3>

    <CodeBlock
      code={`# Update the system
apt update && apt upgrade -y

# Install Docker
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com | sh

# Verify Docker is working
docker --version`}
      language="bash"
      filename="Terminal (VPS)"
    />

    <h3>3. Install OpenClaw</h3>

    <CodeBlock
      code={`# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw.git
cd openclaw

# Run the Docker setup
docker compose up -d`}
      language="bash"
      filename="Terminal (VPS)"
    />

    <h3>4. Initial configuration</h3>

    <p>Once OpenClaw is running, access the configuration interface:</p>

    <CodeBlock
      code={`# Open the interactive configuration interface
docker exec -it openclaw npx openclaw`}
      language="bash"
      filename="Terminal (VPS)"
    />

    <p>This will open an interactive wizard where you can:</p>

    <ol>
      <li>Select <strong>"QuickStart"</strong> for quick setup</li>
      <li>Choose your AI provider (Claude, GPT-4o, Gemini, etc.)</li>
      <li>Connect your messaging platform</li>
      <li>Enable "skills" (plugins) like file system access, browser, etc.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section id="claude-pro">
    <h2>Connect with Claude Pro</h2>

    <p>OpenClaw can use your Claude Pro/Max subscription directly. You have two options:</p>

    <h3>Option A: Anthropic API Key (recommended)</h3>

    <p>The most stable and controlled approach:</p>

    <ol>
      <li>Go to <a href="https://console.anthropic.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">console.anthropic.com</a></li>
      <li>Create an API Key in Settings → API Keys</li>
      <li>In OpenClaw's configuration, select "Anthropic" as provider</li>
      <li>Enter your API Key</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="callout callout-warning">
      <p><strong>Note about costs:</strong> The Anthropic API is charged per usage (tokens), separate from your Claude Pro subscription. If you prefer to use your existing subscription, see Option B.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Option B: Claude Max API Proxy</h3>

    <p>OpenClaw includes a proxy that lets you use your Claude Max subscription directly:</p>

    <ol>
      <li>In OpenClaw's configuration, select <strong>"Claude Max API Proxy"</strong></li>
      <li>Log in with your Anthropic account</li>
      <li>OpenClaw will automatically configure a daemon that maintains the connection</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="callout callout-warning">
      <p><strong>Important warning:</strong> Anthropic may cancel your subscription if they detect excessive or automated usage through the proxy. Every agent action is an API call. Use this option moderately and monitor your usage.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="messaging">
    <h2>Connect Messaging Platform</h2>

    <p>This is the fun part - connecting OpenClaw to the messaging app you use every day.</p>

    <h3>Telegram (easiest)</h3>

    <ol>
      <li>Open Telegram and search for <strong>@BotFather</strong></li>
      <li>Send <code>/newbot</code> and follow the instructions to create a bot</li>
      <li>Copy the token that BotFather gives you</li>
      <li>In OpenClaw's configuration, select "Telegram" and paste the token</li>
      <li>Now you can talk to your AI from Telegram</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>WhatsApp</h3>

    <ol>
      <li>In OpenClaw's configuration, select "WhatsApp"</li>
      <li>Scan the QR code that appears with your phone</li>
      <li>OpenClaw connects to WhatsApp Web and receives your messages</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Discord</h3>

    <ol>
      <li>Go to the <a href="https://discord.com/developers/applications" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Discord Developer Portal</a></li>
      <li>Create a new application and bot</li>
      <li>Copy the bot token</li>
      <li>In OpenClaw, select "Discord" and paste the token</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="callout">
      <p><strong>Other platforms:</strong> OpenClaw also supports Slack, Signal, iMessage, Microsoft Teams, Google Chat, and Matrix. Check the <a href="https://docs.openclaw.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">official documentation</a> for instructions on each one.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="security">
    <h2>Security and Best Practices</h2>

    <p>OpenClaw is powerful, but giving an AI agent access to your server requires precautions:</p>

    <div class="callout callout-warning">
      <p><strong>Important:</strong> Security researchers have identified risks in OpenClaw. Follow these practices to protect your server and data.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Security recommendations</h3>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Use a dedicated VPS</strong> - Don't install OpenClaw on your personal computer or a server with sensitive data. An isolated $5/month VPS is the best option</li>
      <li><strong>Don't give root access</strong> - Configure a non-privileged user for OpenClaw</li>
      <li><strong>Review Skills carefully</strong> - Don't install skills from unverified sources. Malicious skills that steal credentials have been found</li>
      <li><strong>Monitor API usage</strong> - Agent loops can generate unexpected costs. Set spending limits on your AI provider</li>
      <li><strong>Update regularly</strong> - Keep OpenClaw and Docker up to date</li>
      <li><strong>Configure a firewall</strong> - Only open the ports you need</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Basic firewall setup</h3>

    <CodeBlock
      code={`# Configure UFW (firewall)
ufw allow ssh
ufw allow 80/tcp
ufw allow 443/tcp
ufw enable`}
      language="bash"
      filename="Terminal (VPS)"
    />

    <h3>Create non-privileged user</h3>

    <CodeBlock
      code={`# Create user for OpenClaw
adduser openclaw
usermod -aG docker openclaw

# Switch to the new user
su - openclaw`}
      language="bash"
      filename="Terminal (VPS)"
    />
  </section>

  <div class="callout">
    <p><strong>Additional resources:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub - OpenClaw</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://docs.openclaw.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Official documentation</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://docs.openclaw.ai/providers/claude-max-api-proxy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Claude Max API Proxy guide</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="next-section">
    <a href="/en/prompts" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">
      Next: Prompts & Tips →
    </a>
  </div>
</ContentLayout>

